summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming previous resolutions and statements on the situation between Ethiopia and Eritrea,
Stressing commitment to the peace process and Algiers Agreements implementation,
Bearing in mind progress in EEBC meeting and anticipating a positive outcome in the next meeting,

1. Extends UNMEE's mandate until 31 May 2006;
2. Demands parties' full compliance with resolution 1640 (2005), particularly paragraphs 1 and 5;
3. Calls on Member States to support UNMEE and contribute to the Trust Fund for demarcation;
4. Threatens to adjust UNMEE's mandate and troop level by end of May 2006 if parties don't comply;
5. Requests the Secretary-General to report on parties' compliance within 7 days and provide recommendations;
6. Remains seized of the matter.
